+ - **[irobot_performance_test_factory](irobot_performance_test_factory)**: this package provides the `irobot_performance_test_factory::TemplateFactory` class that can be used to create `irobot_performance_test::PerformanceNode` objects with specific publishers and subscriptions according to some arguments provided at runtime: this can be done through json files or command line options.
+ The interfaces (msg and srv) that can be used in these nodes have to be defined in the so called `irobot_performance_test_factory_plugins`.
+ - **[irobot_performance_test_plugin_cmake](irobot_performance_test_plugin_cmake)**: this package provides the CMake function used to generate a factory plugin from interfaces definitions.
+ - **[irobot_interfaces_plugin](irobot_interfaces_plugin)**: this package is a `irobot_performance_test_factory_plugin` that provides all the interfaces used in the iRobot system topologies.
  - **[irobot_benchmark](irobot_benchmark)**: this package provides our main benchmark application.
  This executable can load one or multiple json topologies and it creates a ROS2 system running in a specific process from each of them.
  It also contains sample json topologies.
